class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534136\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534136\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 15, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yla1665702916470.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yla1665702916470.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yla1665702916470.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yla1665702916470\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Provide Uniface with DBMS and connector characteristics, or supply logon\n    information.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yla1665702916470__section_m13_zlw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1063159e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Refer to the following modes for the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Info</code> request:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15527e1_d15528e1_d15529e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Modes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15527e1_d15528e1_d15529e1__entry__1\">Mode </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15527e1_d15528e1_d15529e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15527e1_d15528e1_d15529e1__entry__1\">Mode 0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15527e1_d15528e1_d15529e1__entry__2\">Provide Uniface with DBMS and connector\n                characteristics by filling in all applicable elements of the  <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinfo</code>\n                structure. <p class=\"p\">The mode 0 Info request must be successful and return 0 to\n                  Uniface.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15527e1_d15528e1_d15529e1__entry__1\">Mode 1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15527e1_d15528e1_d15529e1__entry__2\">Provide Uniface with the user name and password\n                corresponding to the current logon path. <p class=\"p\">If the connector is not capable of\n                  providing logon information, return -1 to Uniface.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yla1665702916470__section_gxs_x3x_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1063159e117\">From Uniface</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Preconditions realized by Uniface—When the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Info</code> request is called in mode\n        1, there is an established logon path.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Information Available from Uniface</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__1\">Data Structure-&gt;Element</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__3\">Modes</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;umisc</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__2\">Address of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinfo</code>\n                structure.</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__3\">All Modes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uinfo-&gt;mode</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__2\">Requested mode of the Info request.</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__3\">All Modes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrvini</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__2\">Unique identification of the current logon\n                path.</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__3\">Mode 1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;iobuf</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__2\">Points to the general I/O buffer.</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__3\">Mode 1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;sqlbuf</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__2\">Points to the SQL buffer.</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15530e1_d15531e1_d15532e1__entry__3\">Mode 1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yla1665702916470__section_afg_y3x_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1063159e235\">To Uniface</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Mode information related to the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Info</code> request, and the connector request\n        return values.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15533e1_d15534e1_d15535e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 3. </span><span class=\"title\">Modes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15533e1_d15534e1_d15535e1__entry__1\">Mode</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15533e1_d15534e1_d15535e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15533e1_d15534e1_d15535e1__entry__1\">Mode 0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15533e1_d15534e1_d15535e1__entry__2\">All applicable elements of the <code class=\"ph codeph\">uinfo</code>\n                structure must be given a value. Elements that are not given a value will have a\n                default value of 0. This is an appropriate default for all non-mandatory elements.\n                  <p class=\"p\">The connector request return value must be 0; do not change the value of\n                    <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrverr</code>.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15533e1_d15534e1_d15535e1__entry__1\">Mode 1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15533e1_d15534e1_d15535e1__entry__2\">Store the user name and password corresponding to the\n                current logon path as two contiguous null-terminated strings in the general I/O\n                buffer. For example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">scott/0tiger/0</code>\n<p class=\"p\">Any of the two strings may be empty, but the two NULL characters (‘/0’ in ‘C’)\n                  must be present.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 4. </span><span class=\"title\">Connector Request Return Values</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1__entry__1\">Value </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1__entry__2\">Logon information is provided in the general I/O\n                buffer.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1__entry__1\">-1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1__entry__2\">Logon information is not available.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1__entry__1\">-9</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1__entry__2\">I/O server logon error.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yla1665702916470__p_d130220e1_d130221e1_d130222e1\">If the connector request return value is less than 0,\n        a connector error code must be supplied in <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrverr</code>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yla1665702916470__section_h1n_xmw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1063159e369\">Service Functions</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Not applicable.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yla1665702916470__section_xd5_fmw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1063159e378\">Extra information</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yla1665702916470__p_d130232e1_d130233e1_d130234e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">Info</code> request is provided with a\n        dummy control block. This control block does not describe a table and it does not have an\n        associated connector workspace.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15539e1_d15540e1_d15541e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 5. </span><span class=\"title\">Modes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15539e1_d15540e1_d15541e1__entry__1\">Mode</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15539e1_d15540e1_d15541e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15539e1_d15540e1_d15541e1__entry__1\">Mode 0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15539e1_d15540e1_d15541e1__entry__2\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">Info</code> request can be called\n                several times. Identical characteristics must be provided with each call. No special\n                initialization should be performed in the request. <p class=\"p\">If incorrect or inconsistent\n                  values are provided to Uniface, very obscure errors can occur in further\n                  processing.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15539e1_d15540e1_d15541e1__entry__1\"> Mode 1</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yla1665702916470__table_d15539e1_d15540e1_d15541e1__entry__2\">The mode 1 <code class=\"ph codeph\">Info</code> request is called\n                when there is a reference to <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$user</span> or\n                  <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$password</span> in the ProcScript language. <p class=\"p\">The connector may\n                  implement the request for logon information in the following ways:</p><ul class=\"ul\" id=\"yla1665702916470__ul_jpw_jmw_fwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yla1665702916470__li_d46739e1_d46740e1_d46741e1\">Store the information in a static area when\n                    the Logon request is performed.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yla1665702916470__li_d46742e1_d46743e1_d46744e1\">Get the information from the DBMS.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azl1665702915888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uctrl</a><p>Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iga1665702915956.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uinfo</a><p>Supplies Uniface with basic information about the DBMS and the connector.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534136\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534136\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Info ('I') Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 15, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Provide Uniface with DBMS and connector characteristics, or supply logon information. Description Refer to the following modes for the Info request: Table 1. Modes Mode Description Mode 0 Provide Uniface with DBMS and connector characteristics by filling in all applicable elements of the uinfo structure. The mode 0 Info request must be successful and return 0 to Uniface. Mode 1 Provide Uniface with the user name and password corresponding to the current logon path. If the connector is not capable of providing logon information, return -1 to Uniface. From Uniface Preconditions realized by Uniface—When the Info request is called in mode 1, there is an established logon path. Table 2. Information Available from Uniface Data Structure->Element Description Modes uctrl->umisc Address of the uinfo structure. All Modes uinfo->mode Requested mode of the Info request. All Modes uctrl->udrvini Unique identification of the current logon path. Mode 1 uctrl->iobuf Points to the general I/O buffer. Mode 1 uctrl->sqlbuf Points to the SQL buffer. Mode 1 To Uniface Mode information related to the Info request, and the connector request return values. Table 3. Modes Mode Description Mode 0 All applicable elements of the uinfo structure must be given a value. Elements that are not given a value will have a default value of 0. This is an appropriate default for all non-mandatory elements. The connector request return value must be 0; do not change the value of uctrl->udrverr . Mode 1 Store the user name and password corresponding to the current logon path as two contiguous null-terminated strings in the general I/O buffer. For example: scott/0tiger/0 Any of the two strings may be empty, but the two NULL characters (‘/0’ in ‘C’) must be present. Table 4. Connector Request Return Values Value Description 0 Logon information is provided in the general I/O buffer. -1 Logon information is not available. -9 I/O server logon error. If the connector request return value is less than 0, a connector error code must be supplied in uctrl->udrverr . Service Functions Not applicable. Extra information The Info request is provided with a dummy control block. This control block does not describe a table and it does not have an associated connector workspace. Table 5. Modes Mode Description Mode 0 The Info request can be called several times. Identical characteristics must be provided with each call. No special initialization should be performed in the request. If incorrect or inconsistent values are provided to Uniface, very obscure errors can occur in further processing. Mode 1 The mode 1 Info request is called when there is a reference to $user or $password in the ProcScript language. The connector may implement the request for logon information in the following ways: Store the information in a static area when the Logon request is performed. Get the information from the DBMS. Related Links uctrl Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table. uinfo Supplies Uniface with basic information about the DBMS and the connector. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}